review_blob: nice copper to amber color with a good layer of head. big Tropical aroma full och citrus, pineapple, mango and peach. nice mouthfeel with good carbonation. good fruity hop flavours that are balancing the malt sweetness.
beer_name: S:t Eriks & Mathias Dahlgren Winter DIPA

review_blob: Like its sibling blizzard and whiteout it has a milkchocolate like head that settles nicely in the glass. Aroma is overwhelming with chilipepper glad the taste is more balanced with chili, chocolate, coffe, roasted tones and a nice sweetnes. great oily mouthfeel.

Great head light brown, like milk chocolate. Aroma has hints of chili and coffee and even some dark chocolate but could wish for more.Mouthfeel is alright, maybe little thin, some liquorice, in the end it was just a bit to plain.

Light red to brown in colour and pours a milkchocolate colored head. Slight cacao and roasted tones in the aroma. Very fizzy mouthfeel not to my liking and very bitter like dark chocolate, Not at all as good as earlier versions
